
// The code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append the results of [data.read] to the current node. It retrieves nodes using [get-nodes] from the [.arguments] node, specifically targeting [limit] and [offset] arguments, which are likely used for pagination purposes. This setup is useful for dynamically constructing a data retrieval operation with pagination controls.
add:x:./*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/limit
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/offset
